field.value:
To specify custom lifestyle in XML the following is required:
{code}
<component id='a' type='Castle.Windsor.Tests.A' lifestyle='custom' customLifestyleType='CustomLifestyleManager'>
{code}

That seems to go against DRY. The following should be enough
{code}
<component id='a' type='Castle.Windsor.Tests.A' customLifestyleType='CustomLifestyleManager'>
{code}

In other words, when lifestyle attribute is not present, but customLifestyleType is, the custom lifestyle should be used.
